{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Let's just start by looking at some great photographs."},{"time":5000,"text":"This is an icon of National Geographic,"},{"time":8000,"text":"an Afghan refugee taken by Steve McCurry."},{"time":11000,"text":"But the Harvard Lampoon is about to come out"},{"time":14000,"text":"with a parody of National Geographic,"},{"time":16000,"text":"and I shudder to think what they're going to do to this photograph."},{"time":20000,"text":"Oh, the wrath of Photoshop."}]},{"cues":[{"time":24000,"text":"This is a jet landing at San Francisco, by Bruce Dale."},{"time":27000,"text":"He mounted a camera on the tail."},{"time":34000,"text":"A poetic image for a story on Tolstoy, by Sam Abell."},{"time":40000,"text":"Pygmies in the DRC, by Randy Olson."},{"time":42000,"text":"I love this photograph because it reminds me"},{"time":44000,"text":"of Degas' bronze sculptures of the little dancer."},{"time":50000,"text":"A polar bear swimming in the Arctic, by Paul Nicklen."},{"time":55000,"text":"Polar bears need ice to be able to move back and forth --"},{"time":58000,"text":"they're not very good swimmers --"},{"time":60000,"text":"and we know what's happening to the ice."},{"time":64000,"text":"These are camels moving across the Rift Valley in Africa,"},{"time":68000,"text":"photographed by Chris Johns."},{"time":71000,"text":"Shot straight down, so these are the shadows of the camels."},{"time":79000,"text":"This is a rancher in Texas, by William Albert Allard,"},{"time":81000,"text":"a great portraitist."},{"time":85000,"text":"And Jane Goodall, making her own special connection,"},{"time":87000,"text":"photographed by Nick Nichols."},{"time":92000,"text":"This is a soap disco in Spain, photographed by David Alan Harvey."},{"time":96000,"text":"And David said that there was lot of weird stuff"},{"time":98000,"text":"happening on the dance floor."},{"time":100000,"text":"But, hey, at least it's hygienic."},{"time":103000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":107000,"text":"These are sea lions in Australia doing their own dance,"},{"time":111000,"text":"by David Doubilet."},{"time":114000,"text":"And this is a comet, captured by Dr. Euan Mason."},{"time":120000,"text":"And finally, the bow of the Titanic, without movie stars,"},{"time":124000,"text":"photographed by Emory Kristof."},{"time":131000,"text":"Photography carries a power that holds up"},{"time":133000,"text":"under the relentless swirl of today's saturated, media world,"},{"time":137000,"text":"because photographs emulate the way"},{"time":139000,"text":"that our mind freezes a significant moment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":141000,"text":"Here's an example."},{"time":143000,"text":"Four years ago, I was at the beach with my son,"},{"time":145000,"text":"and he was learning how to swim"},{"time":148000,"text":"in this relatively soft surf of the Delaware beaches."},{"time":152000,"text":"But I turned away for a moment, and he got caught into a riptide"},{"time":155000,"text":"and started to be pulled out towards the jetty."},{"time":158000,"text":"I can stand here right now and see,"},{"time":161000,"text":"as I go tearing into the water after him,"},{"time":164000,"text":"the moments slowing down and freezing into this arrangement."},{"time":167000,"text":"I can see the rocks are over here."},{"time":171000,"text":"There's a wave about to crash onto him."},{"time":173000,"text":"I can see his hands reaching out,"},{"time":176000,"text":"and I can see his face in terror,"},{"time":178000,"text":"looking at me, saying, \"Help me, Dad.\""},{"time":182000,"text":"I got him. The wave broke over us."},{"time":184000,"text":"We got back on shore; he was fine."},{"time":186000,"text":"We were a little bit rattled."},{"time":188000,"text":"But this flashbulb memory, as it's called,"},{"time":192000,"text":"is when all the elements came together to define"},{"time":194000,"text":"not just the event, but my emotional connection to it."},{"time":199000,"text":"And this is what a photograph taps into"},{"time":201000,"text":"when it makes its own powerful connection to a viewer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":204000,"text":"Now I have to tell you,"},{"time":206000,"text":"I was talking to Kyle last week about this,"},{"time":208000,"text":"that I was going to tell this story."},{"time":210000,"text":"And he said, \"Oh, yeah, I remember that too!"},{"time":212000,"text":"I remember my image of you"},{"time":214000,"text":"was that you were up on the shore yelling at me.\""},{"time":216000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":218000,"text":"I thought I was a hero."},{"time":220000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":221000,"text":"So,"},{"time":224000,"text":"this represents -- this is a cross-sample of"},{"time":226000,"text":"some remarkable images taken by some of the world's greatest photojournalists,"},{"time":230000,"text":"working at the very top of their craft --"},{"time":233000,"text":"except one."},{"time":235000,"text":"This photograph was taken by Dr. Euan Mason"},{"time":238000,"text":"in New Zealand last year,"},{"time":240000,"text":"and it was submitted and published in National Geographic."},{"time":243000,"text":"Last year, we added a section to our website called \"Your Shot,\""},{"time":245000,"text":"where anyone can submit photographs for possible publication."},{"time":249000,"text":"And it has become a wild success,"},{"time":252000,"text":"tapping into the enthusiast photography community."},{"time":255000,"text":"The quality of these amateur photographs"},{"time":257000,"text":"can, at times, be amazing."},{"time":259000,"text":"And seeing this reinforces, for me,"},{"time":261000,"text":"that every one of us has at least one or two"},{"time":264000,"text":"great photographs in them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":266000,"text":"But to be a great photojournalist,"},{"time":269000,"text":"you have to have more than just one or two"},{"time":271000,"text":"great photographs in you."},{"time":273000,"text":"You've got to be able to make them all the time."},{"time":275000,"text":"But even more importantly,"},{"time":278000,"text":"you need to know how to create a visual narrative."},{"time":281000,"text":"You need to know how to tell a story."},{"time":284000,"text":"So I'm going to share with you some coverages"},{"time":286000,"text":"that I feel demonstrate the storytelling power of photography."}]},{"cues":[{"time":291000,"text":"Photographer Nick Nichols went to document"},{"time":294000,"text":"a very small and relatively unknown wildlife sanctuary"},{"time":297000,"text":"in Chad, called Zakouma."},{"time":300000,"text":"The original intent was to travel there"},{"time":302000,"text":"and bring back a classic story of diverse species,"},{"time":304000,"text":"of an exotic locale."},{"time":306000,"text":"And that is what Nick did, up to a point."},{"time":308000,"text":"This is a serval cat."},{"time":310000,"text":"He's actually taking his own picture,"},{"time":312000,"text":"shot with what's called a camera trap."},{"time":314000,"text":"There's an infrared beam that's going across,"},{"time":316000,"text":"and he has stepped into the beam and taken his photograph."},{"time":318000,"text":"These are baboons at a watering hole."},{"time":323000,"text":"Nick -- the camera, again, an automatic camera"},{"time":325000,"text":"took thousands of pictures of this."},{"time":327000,"text":"And Nick ended up with a lot of pictures"},{"time":329000,"text":"of the rear ends of baboons."},{"time":331000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":332000,"text":"A lion having a late night snack --"},{"time":335000,"text":"notice he's got a broken tooth."},{"time":340000,"text":"And a crocodile walks up a riverbank toward its den."},{"time":343000,"text":"I love this little bit of water"},{"time":345000,"text":"that comes off the back of his tail."}]},{"cues":[{"time":349000,"text":"But the centerpiece species of Zakouma are the elephants."},{"time":352000,"text":"It's one of the largest intact herds in this part of Africa."},{"time":356000,"text":"Here's a photograph shot in moonlight,"},{"time":358000,"text":"something that digital photography has made a big difference for."},{"time":361000,"text":"It was with the elephants that this story pivoted."},{"time":363000,"text":"Nick, along with researcher Dr. Michael Fay,"},{"time":367000,"text":"collared the matriarch of the herd."},{"time":369000,"text":"They named her Annie,"},{"time":371000,"text":"and they began tracking her movements."},{"time":373000,"text":"The herd was safe within the confines of the park,"},{"time":375000,"text":"because of this dedicated group of park rangers."},{"time":377000,"text":"But once the annual rains began,"},{"time":381000,"text":"the herd would begin migrating to feeding grounds outside the park."}]},{"cues":[{"time":384000,"text":"And that's when they ran into trouble."},{"time":387000,"text":"For outside the safety of the park were poachers,"},{"time":389000,"text":"who would hunt them down only for the value of their ivory tusks."},{"time":394000,"text":"The matriarch that they were radio tracking,"},{"time":396000,"text":"after weeks of moving back and forth, in and out of the park,"},{"time":399000,"text":"came to a halt outside the park."},{"time":401000,"text":"Annie had been killed, along with 20 members of her herd."},{"time":409000,"text":"And they only came for the ivory."},{"time":415000,"text":"This is actually one of the rangers."},{"time":417000,"text":"They were able to chase off one of the poachers and recover this ivory,"},{"time":420000,"text":"because they couldn't leave it there,"},{"time":422000,"text":"because it's still valuable."},{"time":424000,"text":"But what Nick did was he brought back"},{"time":426000,"text":"a story that went beyond the old-school method"},{"time":430000,"text":"of just straight, \"Isn't this an amazing world?\""},{"time":432000,"text":"And instead, created a story that touched our audiences deeply."},{"time":436000,"text":"Instead of just knowledge of this park,"},{"time":438000,"text":"he created an understanding and an empathy"},{"time":440000,"text":"for the elephants, the rangers and the many issues"},{"time":442000,"text":"surrounding human-wildlife conflicts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":446000,"text":"Now let's go over to India."},{"time":448000,"text":"Sometimes you can tell a broad story in a focused way."},{"time":451000,"text":"We were looking at the same issue that Richard Wurman"},{"time":454000,"text":"touches upon in his new world population project."},{"time":457000,"text":"For the first time in history,"},{"time":459000,"text":"more people live in urban, rather than rural, environments."},{"time":463000,"text":"And most of that growth is not in the cities,"},{"time":465000,"text":"but in the slums that surround them."},{"time":468000,"text":"Jonas Bendiksen, a very energetic photographer,"},{"time":471000,"text":"came to me and said,"},{"time":473000,"text":"\"We need to document this, and here's my proposal."},{"time":476000,"text":"Let's go all over the world and photograph every single slum around the world.\""},{"time":479000,"text":"And I said, \"Well, you know, that might be a bit ambitious for our budget.\""},{"time":482000,"text":"So instead, what we did was"},{"time":484000,"text":"we decided to, instead of going out and doing what would result"},{"time":487000,"text":"in what we'd consider sort of a survey story --"},{"time":489000,"text":"where you just go in and see just a little bit of everything --"},{"time":492000,"text":"we put Jonas into Dharavi,"},{"time":495000,"text":"which is part of Mumbai, India,"},{"time":497000,"text":"and let him stay there, and really get into"},{"time":499000,"text":"the heart and soul of this really major part of the city."},{"time":506000,"text":"What Jonas did was not just go and do a surface look"},{"time":508000,"text":"at the awful conditions that exist in such places."},{"time":511000,"text":"He saw that this was a living and breathing and vital part"},{"time":514000,"text":"of how the entire urban area functioned."},{"time":517000,"text":"By staying tightly focused in one place,"},{"time":519000,"text":"Jonas tapped into the soul and the enduring human spirit"},{"time":522000,"text":"that underlies this community."},{"time":526000,"text":"And he did it in a beautiful way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":531000,"text":"Sometimes, though, the only way to tell a story is with a sweeping picture."},{"time":534000,"text":"We teamed up underwater photographer Brian Skerry"},{"time":537000,"text":"and photojournalist Randy Olson"},{"time":539000,"text":"to document the depletion of the world's fisheries."},{"time":542000,"text":"We weren't the only ones to tackle this subject,"},{"time":545000,"text":"but the photographs that Brian and Randy created"},{"time":548000,"text":"are among the best to capture both the human"},{"time":550000,"text":"and natural devastation of overfishing."},{"time":552000,"text":"Here, in a photo by Brian,"},{"time":554000,"text":"a seemingly crucified shark is caught up"},{"time":557000,"text":"in a gill net off of Baja."},{"time":559000,"text":"I've seen sort of OK pictures of bycatch,"},{"time":562000,"text":"the animals accidentally scooped up"},{"time":564000,"text":"while fishing for a specific species."},{"time":566000,"text":"But here, Brian captured a unique view"},{"time":568000,"text":"by positioning himself underneath the boat"},{"time":571000,"text":"when they threw the waste overboard."},{"time":577000,"text":"And Brian then went on to even greater risk"},{"time":579000,"text":"to get this never-before-made photograph"},{"time":581000,"text":"of a trawl net scraping the ocean bottom."}]},{"cues":[{"time":586000,"text":"Back on land, Randy Olson photographed"},{"time":588000,"text":"a makeshift fish market in Africa,"},{"time":590000,"text":"where the remains of filleted fish were sold to the locals,"},{"time":593000,"text":"the main parts having already been sent to Europe."},{"time":596000,"text":"And here in China, Randy shot a jellyfish market."},{"time":600000,"text":"As prime food sources are depleted,"},{"time":602000,"text":"the harvest goes deeper into the oceans"},{"time":604000,"text":"and brings in more such sources of protein."},{"time":606000,"text":"This is called fishing down the food chain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":609000,"text":"But there are also glimmers of hope,"},{"time":611000,"text":"and I think anytime we're doing a big, big story on this,"},{"time":614000,"text":"we don't really want to go"},{"time":616000,"text":"and just look at all the problems."},{"time":618000,"text":"We also want to look for solutions."},{"time":619000,"text":"Brian photographed a marine sanctuary in New Zealand,"},{"time":623000,"text":"where commercial fishing had been banned --"},{"time":625000,"text":"the result being that the overfished species have been restored,"},{"time":629000,"text":"and with them a possible solution for sustainable fisheries."}]},{"cues":[{"time":632000,"text":"Photography can also compel us to confront"},{"time":635000,"text":"issues that are potentially distressing and controversial."},{"time":638000,"text":"James Nachtwey, who was honored at last year's TED,"},{"time":642000,"text":"took a look at the sweep of the medical system"},{"time":644000,"text":"that is utilized to handle the American wounded coming out of Iraq."},{"time":647000,"text":"It is like a tube where a wounded soldier enters on one end"},{"time":650000,"text":"and exits back home, on the other."},{"time":653000,"text":"Jim started in the battlefield."},{"time":655000,"text":"Here, a medical technician tends to a wounded soldier"},{"time":659000,"text":"on the helicopter ride back to the field hospital."},{"time":662000,"text":"Here is in the field hospital."},{"time":664000,"text":"The soldier on the right has the name of his daughter"},{"time":667000,"text":"tattooed across his chest, as a reminder of home."},{"time":670000,"text":"From here, the more severely wounded are transported"},{"time":674000,"text":"back to Germany, where they meet up with their families"},{"time":676000,"text":"for the first time."},{"time":681000,"text":"And then back to the States to recuperate at veterans' hospitals,"},{"time":685000,"text":"such as here in Walter Reed."},{"time":687000,"text":"And finally, often fitted with high-tech prosthesis,"},{"time":689000,"text":"they exit the medical system and attempt"},{"time":691000,"text":"to regain their pre-war lives."},{"time":693000,"text":"Jim took what could have been a straight-up medical science story"},{"time":696000,"text":"and gave it a human dimension that touched our readers deeply."}]},{"cues":[{"time":702000,"text":"Now, these stories are great examples"},{"time":704000,"text":"of how photography can be used"},{"time":706000,"text":"to address some of our most important topics."},{"time":709000,"text":"But there are also times when photographers"},{"time":711000,"text":"simply encounter things that are, when it comes down to it,"},{"time":713000,"text":"just plain fun."},{"time":715000,"text":"Photographer Paul Nicklin traveled to Antarctica"},{"time":717000,"text":"to shoot a story on leopard seals."},{"time":719000,"text":"They have been rarely photographed, partly because they are considered"},{"time":722000,"text":"one of the most dangerous predators in the ocean."},{"time":725000,"text":"In fact, a year earlier, a researcher had been"},{"time":727000,"text":"grabbed by one and pulled down to depth and killed."},{"time":729000,"text":"So you can imagine Paul was maybe a little bit hesitant"},{"time":731000,"text":"about getting into the water."},{"time":734000,"text":"Now, what leopard seals do mostly is, they eat penguins."},{"time":737000,"text":"You know of \"The March of the Penguins.\""},{"time":739000,"text":"This is sort of the munch of the penguins."},{"time":741000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":744000,"text":"Here a penguin goes up to the edge and looks out"},{"time":747000,"text":"to see if the coast is clear."},{"time":749000,"text":"And then everybody kind of runs out and goes out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":755000,"text":"But then Paul got in the water."},{"time":757000,"text":"And he said he was never really afraid of this."},{"time":760000,"text":"Well, this one female came up to him."},{"time":762000,"text":"She's probably -- it's a shame you can't see it in the photograph,"},{"time":765000,"text":"but she's 12 feet long."},{"time":767000,"text":"So, she is pretty significant in size."},{"time":770000,"text":"And Paul said he was never really afraid,"},{"time":771000,"text":"because she was more curious about him than threatened."},{"time":774000,"text":"This mouthing behavior, on the right,"},{"time":776000,"text":"was really her way of saying to him, \"Hey, look how big I am!\""},{"time":779000,"text":"Or you know, \"My, what big teeth you have.\""},{"time":782000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":783000,"text":"Then Paul thinks that she simply took pity on him."},{"time":785000,"text":"To her, here was this big, goofy creature in the water"},{"time":789000,"text":"that for some reason didn't seem to be interested"},{"time":791000,"text":"in chasing penguins."},{"time":793000,"text":"So what she did was she started to bring penguins to him,"},{"time":797000,"text":"alive, and put them in front of him."},{"time":800000,"text":"She dropped them off, and then they would swim away."},{"time":803000,"text":"She'd kind of look at him, like \"What are you doing?\""},{"time":805000,"text":"Go back and get them, and then bring them back"},{"time":808000,"text":"and drop them in front of him."},{"time":810000,"text":"And she did this over the course of a couple of days,"},{"time":813000,"text":"until the point where she got so frustrated with him"},{"time":815000,"text":"that she started putting them directly on top of his head."},{"time":818000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":820000,"text":"Which just resulted in a fantastic photograph."},{"time":823000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":826000,"text":"Eventually, though, Paul thinks that she just figured"},{"time":829000,"text":"that he was never going to survive."},{"time":831000,"text":"This is her just puffing out, you know,"},{"time":834000,"text":"snorting out in disgust."},{"time":836000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":838000,"text":"And lost interest with him, and went back to what she does best."}]},{"cues":[{"time":841000,"text":"Paul set out to photograph a relatively"},{"time":843000,"text":"mysterious and unknown creature,"},{"time":845000,"text":"and came back with not just a collection of photographs,"},{"time":847000,"text":"but an amazing experience and a great story."},{"time":851000,"text":"It is these kinds of stories,"},{"time":853000,"text":"ones that go beyond the immediate or just the superficial"},{"time":856000,"text":"that demonstrate the power of photojournalism."},{"time":859000,"text":"I believe that photography can make a real connection to people,"},{"time":864000,"text":"and can be employed as a positive agent"},{"time":867000,"text":"for understanding the challenges and opportunities"},{"time":869000,"text":"facing our world today."},{"time":871000,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":872000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}